Gregg Schill
Co-Founder & Senior Managing Director
Mr. Schill serves as Co-Founder & Senior Managing Director of CION Investment Group, LLC as well as a Vice President of CION Ares Diversified Credit Fund (“CADC”).  He joined CION in 2001. Gregg served as Vice President of Treasury and Operations from 2006 to 2011, as Senior Vice President of Treasury and Operations from 2011 to 2012 and since 2012, currently serves as Managing Director of Financial Operations.
He is responsible for various financial and operational aspects of CION and its managed funds. Specifically he focuses on both corporate and portfolio capital structures, budgeting, liquidity, SEC reporting and financial statement review. Mr. Schill received his B.A. in Economics from Columbia University.




