He is responsible for compliance matters pertaining to the distribution of products sponsored by CION Investment Group and its affiliates. He received a B.S from St. John’s University, a J.D. from Albany Law School and an MBA (Finance) from Fordham University. He currently holds the FINRA Series 7, 24, 63 and 65 licenses as well as the Certified Regulatory Compliance Professional (“CRCP”) designation issued jointly by FINRA and the University of Pennsylvania (Wharton School).
