Derek Schwartz
Senior Vice President & National Sales Manager
Derek Schwartz is Senior Vice President and National Sales Manager for CION Securities. He has 20 years of experience working in the financial service and investment industry. Mr. Schwartz began his career in the financial industry in 1996 as a financial specialist with AXA financial, serving clients in the estate planning and business continuity markets by providing complex insurance and investment strategies.
He later joined Merrill Lynch in its large retail NYC complex where he worked as a financial consultant to high net worth business owners and entrepreneurs, offering investment advice and asset allocation strategies in the equity, bond, and alternative markets. Mr. Schwartz also spent over 6 years with Citigroup Asset Management, which was later sold to Legg Mason, working in its sales and distribution business where he assisted in the build out of third party sales in its mutual funds, closed-ends, separately managed accounts, and alternative strategies. In 2008, Mr. Schwartz joined CION Securities as Regional Vice President for sales in the Mid-Atlantic region. In 2013, Mr. Schwartz was named head of U.S. Sales for CION Securities. Since joining CION Securities, Mr. Schwartz has played a vital role in the development, marketing, and sales for numerous alternative investments funds including private debt, real estate, energy, and business development funds.
